              <h3 property="dc:title" datatype="" class="comment-title">
        <a href="/comment/22507#comment-22507" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">Hello Ktk!</a>              </h3>
        
      </header>

  <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/articles/2012/12/Pay-Me-Bug-getting-new-cover" class="rdf-meta"></span><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>I am clearly out of my element.  As an INTP, the first thing I noticed was that the atmosphere didn't seem right.  Then I wondered about the effects the orbital distance would have on the rendering of the thin layer of air.  Not being all that visual, I had to go look up Apollo 16's photos of Earth from a similar perspective - to test my memory.  Of course, I was wrong.  Have a look at <a href="http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/imgcat/hires/a16_h_118_18873.gif">http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/imgcat/hires/a16_h_118_18873.gif</a></p>
<p>Kudos Garth, from a mega space freak, er... geek.</p>
<p>Oh, and Ktk looks cool too :-)  I like how its 'fingers' are flexible.</p>
