  <header>
    <p class="submitted">
            <span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2012-12-12T01:38:02-05:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator"><span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/user/christopher-wright" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name">Christopher Wright</span> replied on <time pubdate datetime="2012-12-12T01:38:02-05:00">Wed, 2012-12-12 01:38</time></span>      <a href="/comment/22510#comment-22510" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">Permalink</a>    </p>

              <h3 property="dc:title" datatype="" class="comment-title">
        <a href="/comment/22510#comment-22510" class="permalink" rel="bookmark">eBooks as well</a>              </h3>
        
      </header>

  <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/articles/2012/12/Pay-Me-Bug-getting-new-cover" class="rdf-meta"></span><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>The eBook will also have the new cover, yes. I might bump up the eBook price to around $5.00... apparently the pendulum is swinging the other direction and people are staying away from eBooks that are too cheap. Which is odd, but there you are.</p>
<p>The price of the paperback... I'm not entirely sure at this point. I'm aiming for $12, but it all depends on how much CreateSpace says it's going to cost to print, which depends on page count. I'm currently building the book all over again (to incorporate typo corrections) and it's a slow and frustrating process.</p>
<p>I was hoping to have it ready before Christmas, but it doesn't look like it's going to make it because I need to print a test copy and make sure everything's right. My timing is impeccable...</p>
</div></div></div>
  
